This folder contains all the tests related to `check_pgactivity`.

# Environment

The tests depend on some PostgreSQL perl modules and `pg_regress` binary. In
PostgreSQL source tree, they are located in `src/test/perl` and
`src/test/regress/pg_regress` (after building for the later).

On Debian, they are installed by package `postgresql-client-$MAJ`.
ON EL, they are installed by package `postgresql$MAJ-devel` (PGDG packages
seem broken though).

Once you installed one of these packages, dependencies can be found using:

~~~
$(pg_config --pkglibdir)/pgxs/src/test/perl/
$(pg_config --pkglibdir)/pgxs/src/test/regress/pg_regress
~~~

To setup your environment:

~~~
PG_REGRESS="$(pg_config --pkglibdir)/pgxs/src/test/regress/pg_regress"
PERL5LIB="$(pg_config --pkglibdir)/pgxs/src/test/perl/:$PERL5LIB"
export PG_REGRESS PERL5LIB
~~~

# run

Tests must be run from the root folder of the project using `perl` or `prove`:

~~~console
~/git/check_pgactivity$ PG_REGRESS="$(pg_config --pkglibdir)/pgxs/src/test/regress/pg_regress"
~/git/check_pgactivity$ PERL5LIB="$(pg_config --pkglibdir)/pgxs/src/test/perl/:$PERL5LIB"
~/git/check_pgactivity$ export PG_REGRESS PERL5LIB

~/git/check_pgactivity$ perl t/01-connection.t
ok 1 - check_cnx status (got 0 vs expected 0)
ok 2 - check_cnx stdout /(?^:POSTGRES_CONNECTION OK: Connection successful)/
1..2

~/git/check_pgactivity$ prove
t/00-copyright-year.t .. ok   
t/01-connection.t ...... ok   
t/10-streaming.t ....... ok    
All tests successful.
Files=3, Tests=21,  3 wallclock secs ( 0.02 usr  0.01 sys +  1.94 cusr  0.58 csys =  2.55 CPU)
Result: PASS
~~~

If tests are failing, log files are kept under `tmp_check/` folder.
